{"id":"278801168_The_ARTES_bilingual_LSP_dictionary_From_collocation_to_higher_order_phraseology","abstract":"Because of globalisation, the requirements for bilingual LSP dictionaries have expanded dramatically, requiring more and more information for users. This chapter deals with the theoretical and practical approaches to introducing bilingual collocations and higher order phraseology in a bilingual term base/ dictionary for specialised translators and domain specialists, learners and professionals. The ARTES online bilingual LSP dictionary is described in detail, showing how it is adapted to target different users by providing both a term base and an electronic dictionary. Corpus data show that linguistic information must go beyond the terminological or lexical levels and include semantic and pragmatic information, stepping thus into the domain of discourse. Finally, solutions for implementing semantic preference and semantic prosody in the dictionary are put forward. © Editorial matter and organization Sylviane Granger and Magali Paquot 2012 © The chapters their several authors 2012. All rights reserved.","authors":["Mojca Pecman","Natalie Kübler"],"meta":["November 2012","DOI:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199654864.003.0010","ISBN: 9780199654864"],"references":["281880499_Working_with_different_corpora_in_translation_teaching","277847833_Extraction_d'une_phraseologie_bilingue_en_langue_de_specialite_corpus_paralleles_et_corpus_comparables","276233080_Le_facteur_local_comme_levier_d'une_traductologie_pragmatique","266462695_The_Kicktionary_-A_Multilingual_Resource_of_the_Language_of_Football","266395248_From_dictionary_to_phrasebook","266393365_Fonctions_lexicales_pour_representer_les_relations_semantiques_entre_termes","265421476_Disentangling_the_phraseological_web","265065730_The_translation_of_domain-specific_languages_and_multilingual_terminology_management","263226050_Semantic_prosody_and_specialised_translation_or_how_a_lexico-grammatical_theory_of_language_can